            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The best way to understand how much weight is carried on the thighs is to sit on your horse bareback. Many un-knowledgeable people will tell you that riding bareback is “cruel” to the horse as all your weight is concentrated into your seat bones which then create huge pressure on the horse’s sensitive back structures. Those of us who have done it (and I, for one, rode bareback for many years on my Arab) will tell you that the weight is spread over a broad area with a lot on the thighs.",
