              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "It is not the purpose of this book to talk about aids as they are well covered in other literature, save one point. In French “Aider” means “to help”  – so aids are not instructions, they are “helps” – ways of helping or enabling (allowing) our horse. Think - how can I help my horse to understand? What are the choices? What are the likely consequences of each choice? Make your choice and be definite. Follow through to understand whether it worked and if not why not. On and on and on... never ending.",
