                    "text": "Tension",
                    "id": "1941160482727"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "text": "Muscular tension in the rider can be caused by either mental or physical problems. Low confidence leaves us fearful and tense (literally clinging on with our muscles). The feeling in our mind involuntarily affects our body and leads to hard muscles. In turn this means that the horse is blocked by the rider and is tense also. Muscle tension can also result from injury.  The body tenses involuntarily to protect itself. Once again the horse is blocked by the rider and is tense also. ",
                    "id": "1198912424576"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "text": "High levels of confidence can bring similar problems. Such self belief can lead to domination (“he will do this”) and force.  This can lead to voluntarily tensed and hard muscles.  In turn this means that the horse is blocked by the rider. At times I have indulged in this behaviour. “I must make him do this…by now I should be doing this”…but fail to recognise what I or the horse feel like today and that it isn’t going to be possible. This is a recipe for frustration and anger.  I’m sure we have all been there.",
