              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Definiteness is not about being apologetic. It is not about being forceful. It is about being clear and consistent. The problem often seen is that the rider does not feel confident enough to correct the horse when she herself feels she may be the cause of the problem. Eyes on the ground can help to check that you are sitting straight and so on. Often it is just that the lack of confidence results in a lack of definiteness and the horse just thinks it’s ok. The rider knows it isn’t and blames themself again.",
