                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "text": "Feedback is vital to all systems. Balancing loops, in particular, are a force for equilibrium; they prevent things getting out of control. Biological balancing loops are geared to survival. For example, when it gets too hot I will sweat which in turn cools me down. When we humans wish to control (or manage the performance of) something we design balancing loops. Usually these loops have a variable we want to influence. We set a target value for that variable and we monitor the gap between the actual value and the target. When the actual is below target we take action to improve the actual value. When we are on-target we reward the achievement in some way; this may mean that we simply cease acting! ",
