                    "text": "When we connect the rein to a bit at one end and the rider’s hand at the other we have the possibility of various forces affecting the shape of the rein – gravity (downwards); the weight of the horses head and neck (downwards); and, a balancing force attributable to the rider’s arms. An even greater force can be executed by horse or rider, for example, when the horse attempts to lean on the bit or falls against the rein and the same for the rider. Some riders can be seen to use the reins as a water skier would use the rope.",
